    <h1>My Top 10 Favorites Songs (One Direction)</h1>
    <div class="grid-container">
        <div class="box">
            <h2>1</h2>
            <h2>What Makes You Beautiful</h2>
            <img src="what makes you beautiful.jpg">
            <p>""What Makes You Beautiful" by One Direction is an upbeat pop song released in 2011 as the band's debut single. It celebrates natural beauty and self-confidence, with lyrics reassuring a girl that she’s beautiful even if she doesn’t see it herself. </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>2</h2>
            <h2>Story of My Life</h2> <br>
            <img src="Story of My Life.png">
            <p>""Story of My Life" by One Direction is an emotional folk-pop ballad from their 2013 album Midnight Memories. The song reflects on memories, personal struggles, and the passage of time, with heartfelt lyrics and a poignant melody.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
            <h2>3</h2>
            <h2>Night Changes</h2> <br>
            <img src="Night Change.png">
            <p>"Night Changes" by One Direction is a heartfelt ballad from their 2014 album Four. The song reflects on how time passes and things change, but love remains constant.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>4</h2>
            <h2>Best Song Ever</h2> <br>
            <img src="Best song ever.jpg">
            <p>"Best Song Ever" by One Direction is an energetic pop-rock anthem released in 2013. With a catchy melody, powerful vocals, and fun lyrics, the song is about an unforgettable night and a song that makes it even more special.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
            <h2>5</h2>
            <h2>One Thing</h2> <br>
            <img src="One Thing.jpg">
            <p>"One Thing" by One Direction is an upbeat pop-rock song from their 2011 album Up All Night. With a catchy melody and energetic chorus, the song expresses the feeling of being captivated by someone who has that "one thing" that makes them irresistible.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>6</h2>
            <h2>Drag Me Down</h2> <br>
            <img src="Drug me down.png">
            <p>"Drag Me Down" is an energetic pop-rock anthem released in 2015 as the band's first single after Zayn Malik's departure. The song features a powerful beat, bold lyrics, and strong vocals, emphasizing resilience and unwavering support from loved ones.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
            <h2>7</h2>
            <h2>Kiss You</h2> <br>
            <img src="Kiss you.jpg">
            <p>"Kiss You" by One Direction is a fun and energetic pop song from their 2012 album Take Me Home. With playful lyrics and a catchy beat, the song is about excitement and desire in a relationship, urging someone to take a chance on love.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>8</h2>
            <h2>Live While We're Young</h2>
            <img src="One_Direction_–_Live_While_We're_Young.jpg">
            <p>"Live While We're Young" by One Direction is an upbeat and energetic pop anthem from their 2012 album Take Me Home. The song encourages living in the moment, having fun, and embracing youth without worries.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
            <h2>9</h2>
            <h2>Little Things</h2> <br>
            <img src="One_Direction_-_Little_Things.png">
            <p>"Little Things" by One Direction is a heartfelt acoustic ballad from their 2012 album Take Me Home. Written by Ed Sheeran, the song highlights the small, imperfect details that make someone special and loved.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>10</h2>
            <h2>Steal My Girl</h2> <br>
            <img src="One_Direction_-_Steal_My_Girl.png">
            <p>"Steal My Girl" by One Direction is an anthemic pop-rock song from their 2014 album Four. With a powerful chorus and uplifting melody, the song tells the story of a guy expressing pride and devotion to his girlfriend, claiming that no one else can take her away.</p>
        </div>
